text: Asia is great for many reasons but none
more than the mouth-watering foods you
can find at a very cheap price after
spending most of the last six years
living and traveling through Asia here
are the 10 cheapest meals you can get
for under $1 number 1 Fah Viet Nam's
finest Fah is a clear soup with piping
hot rice noodles herbs and chicken or
beef it's a common Street food around
the country too hot where you will dine
on little plastic chairs right on the
food side 1 number 2 Momo's native to
Bhutan and Nepal Momo's are the most
delicious steamed dumplings you'll ever
have you can get any kind of meat or
even cheese inside dip it in hot sauce
and enjoy especially on a cold winter
day number 3 Pad Thai my favorite Thai
Street food is Pad Thai and I eat it
about twice a week it's a stir-fry of
rice noodles with eggs chopped tofu
dried shrimp garlic bean sprouts chilies
and lime juice it's simply the best
number for Fuuka Fuuka or pani puri is
an indian / Bangladeshi street food that
is like a crispy hollow bread with
flavored water chili potatoes and
chickpeas inside so this is the sweet
tamarind sauce sour lemon sauce
they might upset your stomach but it's
absolutely worth it number 5 esau number
Kisa or grilled chicken intestines is
the epitome of Filipino Street food it
sounds gross but the intestines are
cleaned turned inside out and then
shoved on a stick dip it in vinegar and
enjoy number 6 nasi goreng this is any
variation of fried rice in Indonesia but
what sets it apart is the aromatic
earthy and smoky flavor so if you ever
see someone cooking on a big walk on the
street it's in your best interest to go
number 7 nasi lemak this is Malaysian
crispy chicken with coconut rice it's
commonly eaten throughout the day and
the lines become outrageously long at
the famous places during lunchtime I'm
craving nasi lemak
more than anything in this video number
8 fish amok fish amok is the famous
Cambodian dish which is a thick coconut
based soup with vegetables eggs and fish
eaten with steamed rice sometimes it's
even served inside of a coconut number 9
green curry in the same family as fish
amok green curry is a coconut based
curry with eggplant green curry paste
palm sugar and lots of chilies it's my
favorite Thai dish and I think I'll have
it for lunch today
number 10 char kway chow you cannot go
to Singapore without trying char kway
teow it's a stir-fry of flat rice
noodles dark soy sauce chilies prawns
bean sprouts and served on a banana leaf
it's not the healthiest dish around but
it will surely make you happy so as you
can see if there's anything that Asia
does better than the rest of the world
it is eating for cheap every dish listed
above can be found for less than one
dollar and I hope you get the chance to
go and try them for yourself
